  "response": "Google has experienced several setbacks and failures throughout its history, but one of the most often cited is the failure of Google+. Launched in 2011, Google+ was Google's attempt to create a social networking platform to compete with Facebook. Despite significant investment and integration with other Google services, Google+ struggled to gain substantial user engagement and support. Its complex features and privacy issues further undermined its success. In 2019, Google ultimately announced the shutdown of Google+ for consumers, marking it as one of the company's most notable failures.",
